  - tokens: corresponding list of strings to append when divisor matches
  - mode: concatenation | precedence
  - digit_rule: boolean (if true, apply digit-containment triggers)
  - output_mode: stream | batch
  - start: integer (default 1)
- Implementation tips per language:
  - JavaScript/TypeScript: reuse a single string builder per iteration, push to array or yield via generator for streaming.
  - Python: use list append for batch, yield in generator for streaming; prefer f-strings or str(i) only when needed.
  - Java: use StringBuilder, print via buffered writer for large N.
- Testing guidance:
  - Unit tests: check canonical small ranges (1..15), edge values (3,5,15), and config variants (added divisors, digit rule).
  - Property tests: for random N, verify that each output either equals str(i) or equals the concatenation of tokens for divisors of i.

